bio.singa.mathematics.concepts

Interface MultiDimensional<NumberConcept extends MultiDimensional<NumberConcept>>

  • Type Parameters:
    NumberConcept - The type of the concept that has multiple dimensions.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LabeledMatrix<LabelType>, Matrix, Quaternion, Vector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LabeledRegularMatrix, LabeledSymmetricMatrix, RegularMatrix, RegularQuaternion, RegularVector, Scalar, SquareMatrix, SymmetricMatrix, Vector2D, Vector3D

    public interface MultiDimensional<NumberConcept extends MultiDimensional<NumberConcept>>
    The MultiDimensional interface defines whether a Number concept has one or more Dimensions. It provides methods to compare dimensions of different Objects for calculations, that are dimensional sensitive.

      • assertThatDimensionsMatch

        default void assertThatDimensionsMatch(NumberConcept element)
        Asserts that the given number concept has the same dimension as this vector. If not a IncompatibleDimensionsException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        element - Another number concept.
        Throws:
        IncompatibleDimensionsException - if this number concept has another dimension than the given number concept.
